longBusinessSummary: Glen Eagle Resources Inc. engages in the acquisition, exploration, development, and evaluation of mining properties. The company holds a 100% interest in the Moose Lake phosphate property located in St-Jean Lake area, Quebec; and 80% interest in Piedra Dorada mining concession located in the rich mining district of El Corpus in Honduras. It is also involved in the recovery of gold and silver from tailings; and recovery of gold from rocks. The company was formerly known as Temoris Resources Inc. and changed its name to Glen Eagle Resources Inc. in September 2008. Glen Eagle Resources Inc. is headquartered in Saint-Lambert, Canada.
